# UI Standards

## Components
- Always use Nuxt UI components (@nuxt/ui) when available for consistent UI
- Example of correct usage:
  ```vue
  <UButton color="primary">Click me</UButton>
  ```
- Avoid using raw HTML elements when Nuxt UI components are available
- Never create custom components for functionality that Nuxt UI already provides

## Theming
- Configure all global UI settings in app.config.ts
- Use the following color palette:
  - primary: Main brand color
  - neutral: Text and backgrounds
  - success/info/warning/error: For states
- Use --ui-radius CSS variable for consistent border radius
- Follow Nuxt UI spacing scale

## Styling
- Prefer using ui prop for component customization
- Use Nuxt UI slots for layout customization
- Avoid direct CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Always support dark mode using Nuxt UI's built-in system

@example-component.vue
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const props = defineProps<{
  title: string
}>()
</script>

<template>
  <UCard>
    <UButton
      color="primary"
      :ui="{ 
        base: 'font-semibold',
        padding: 'px-4 py-2'
      }"
    >
      {{ title }}
    </UButton>
  </UCard>
</template>
